ALS poses a tremendous financial cost to patients and families. Financial assistance is often provided by government and independent ALS organizations. 

Government financial assistance
- Social Security Disability Insurance (SSDI)
- Medicare
- Medicaid
- Veterans' Affairs: 

Independent financial assistance


Grants: These are independent organizations that provide "grants" for patients and their families. 

http://JoanDancyAndPALS.org
https://alsrideforlife.org/
https://runs4als.org/
https://www.als.org/massachusetts/about-our-chapter/als-foundation-life-future-20-year-legacy
https://hark-als.org/
https://projectmainst.org/

Donations: go directly to research labs rather than ALS organizations
